Illustration Interpretation of Death - Soulcatcher ‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
Each of us are characters of a story. Every person has their own roles and purposes. When one's role end, death comes. But death is not the end of your story, it's the end of "your part" in that story. Soulcatcher (the Sparrow) pose as the one to transfer your soul to another story, to begin as a new character with a new role. This goes on and on, as the circle of life spins. Soulcatcher is the one to keep the circle intact. 
Do not fear death, for it's the beginning of another chapter in another story.
